==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stupidity
<hw>Stu*pid"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stupiditas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>stupidit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being stupid; extreme dullness
of perception or understanding; insensibility; sluggishness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Stupor; astonishment; stupefaction.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>stupidity</qex>⟦br⟧
Past admiration strikes me, joined with fear.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stupify</ent>⟦br⟧
